{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Shah et al. (2022) presented a system called LM-Nav based on CLIP and GPT-3 for long-horizon navigation through outdoor and complex environments and achieved an 80% success rate in their custom data set.",
    "Similarly, Schumann et al. (2024) proposed VELMA, a model based on CLIP and GPT-4, which uses verbal descriptions of trajectories and visual environment observations as contextual prompts for the next action, and they achieved a task success rate of 23.10% in the Map2seq data set.",
    "Li et al. (2024) introduced VLN-VIDEO, utilizing urban driving videos combined with automatically generated navigation instructions and actions to enhance outdoor VLN performance.",
    "GPT-2 was used to filter out templates with low generation probability.",
    "They gained a 31.7% success rate in the Touchdown data set."
  ],
